div1.p: Of the Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the Counties of King and Kitsap.
The People of the United States of America, to W. H. Harris the Sheriff of King County Greeting:

We command you, that you have the body of C.W. Hutchinson by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said C. W. Hutchinson shall be called or charged, before the HON. ROGER S. GREENE, Judge of the aforesaid Court at the District Court house of King County on the 13th day of November, 1885, at 2 O'Clock P.M to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said C.W. Hutchinson And have you then and there this writ.
WITNESS THE HIN. ROGERS S. GREENE, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 17th day of November A.D. 1885

I hereby certify that I received a writ of Habeas Corpus, of which the within is a true copy on the 12th day of Novemeber 1885, and that I personally served that the same on the same day on C.W. Hutchinson he bring the person to whom said writ is directed, by, delivering to and leaving with him, the said Hutchinson personally, in King County, W.T. said writ.
Sheriff Fees Service 1.00 Copy .80 Travel . 20 Return .50 $2.50
In Re, Application of C.H. Hutchinson for writ of Habeas Corpus
FILED NOV 13 1885 James Seavey, Clerk By James P. Ludlow
Rasin & Gilman Jas Hamilton Lewis pett atty
